lām</i> is mentioned in several places in the Koran, for example at 3:19 ‘Religion with Allah is Islām (peace)’ and 5:3 ‘I have chosen for you Islām (peace) as religion’. This name is often found in combinations, e.g. <i>Nūr al-Islām</i> ‘light of Islam’.","Turkish (<b>İslam</b>): ornamental name from <i>İslam</i> ‘Islam; Muslim’."]},{"name":"Lami","meanings":["Italian: patronymic or plural form of   Lama  .","French (also <b>L'Ami</b>): variant of   Lamy  .","Muslim (Iraq and Maghreb): from a personal name based on Arabic <i>lāmiʿ</i> ‘sparkling, shiny’."]},{"name":"Lalama","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Domenic, Attilio, Donato, Ettore, Gino, Giuseppe, Maddalena, Marcello, Remo.  Spanish Angel, Aida, Carlos, Elena, Jorge, Luis.","Italian (<b>La Lama</b>) and Spanish: variant of   Lama  , with the definite article <i>la</i>. This surname is very rare in Italy (found in Foggia province, Apulia)."]}]},{"name":"Cecilia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Latin name <i>Caecilia</i>, feminine form of <i>Caecilius</i> (  see  Cecil  ). This was a good deal more common than the masculine form, largely due to the fame of the 2nd- or 3rd-century virgin martyr whose name is still mentioned daily in the Roman Catholic Canon of the Mass. She is regarded as the patron saint of music and has inspired works such as  Purcell's  ‘Ode on St Cecilia's Day’, although the reasons for this association are not clear."],"variants":[{"name":"Cecelia","meanings":["From the Latin name <i>Caecilia</i>, feminine form of <i>Caecilius</i> (  see  Cecil  ). This was a good deal more common than the masculine form, largely due to the fame of the 2nd- or 3rd-century virgin martyr whose name is still mentioned daily in the Roman Catholic Canon of the Mass. She is regarded as the patron saint of music and has inspired works such as  Purcell's  ‘Ode on St Cecilia's Day’, although the reasons for this association are not clear."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Cecilia Filipsdotter Folkunga Lama was born in 1365, in Älvsborg, Norrbotten, Sweden, her father, Filip Karlsson Folkunga Lama, was 25 and her mother, Ingeborg Kettilvasta Dotter, was 29. She married Olof Karlsson on 20 January 1381. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 20 January 1435, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1365–20 January 1435":"1365–20. jaanuar 1435","1365–1435":"1365–1435","1371–1428":"1371–1428","1359–Male":"1359–Surnud","1400–1486":"1400–1486","–1469":"–1469","–Female":"Surnud","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1336–1390":"1336–1390","20 January 1435":"20. jaanuar 1435","18. toukokuuta 1428":"18. mai 1428","1340":"1340","1371":"1371","By 20 Jan 1381":"20. jaanuar 1381","Noi 1400":"1400","1390":"1390","31 May 1407":"31. mai 1407","1469":"1469","1359":"1359","1336":"1336","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1365":"1365","1486":"1486","2 February 1390":"2. veebruar 1390","Abt 1390":"umbes 1390","1407":"1407","1428":"1428","Älvsborg, Älvsborgs län, Norrbottens län, Sverige":"Älvsborg, Norrbotten, Rootsi","Finland":"Soome","Villnäs, Lokalks, Turku pori, Finland":"Louhisaari, Turku ja Pori, Soome","Lundas, Edebo, Stockholm, Sweden":"Lundås, Edebo, Stockholm, Rootsi"},"fi":{"1365–20 January 1435":"1365–20. tammikuuta 1435","1365–1435":"1365–1435","1371–1428":"1371–1428","1359–Male":"1359–Kuollut","1400–1486":"1400–1486","–1469":"–1469","–Female":"Kuollut","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1336–1390":"1336–1390","20 January 1435":"20. tammikuuta 1435","18. toukokuuta 1428":"18. toukokuuta 1428","1340":"1340","1371":"1371","By 20 Jan 1381":"20. tammikuuta 1381","Noi 1400":"1400","1390":"1390","31 May 1407":"31. toukokuuta 1407","1469":"1469","1359":"1359","1336":"1336","1435":"1435","1400":"1400","1365":"1365","1486":"1486","2 February 1390":"2. helmikuuta 1390","Abt 1390":"noin 1390","1407":"1407","1428":"1428","Älvsborg, Älvsborgs län, Norrbo